    'projects.hero.subtitle': 'Work Experience & Research Outcomes',
    'projects.hero.title': 'Projects & Research',
    'projects.research.0.desc': '<li><strong>Research Process:</strong> Conducted a comparative study between curcumin and artemisinin, employing a systematic workflow (including extraction, purification, identification, and validation via chromatographic techniques such as HPLC) to achieve traditional Chinese medicine recognition, isolation and purification of active substances, establishment of cellular-level and animal models, as well as analysis of potential clinical medical applications.</li><li><strong>Key Output:</strong> Developed a standardized protocol for the identification of active substances in traditional Chinese medicine, providing technical specifications for subsequent development of medicinal ingredients.</li>',
    'projects.research.0.title': 'Identification of Active Compounds of Chinese Herbal Medicine',
    'projects.research.1.desc': '<li><strong>Research Design:</strong> Analyzed methylmercury-induced neurological disorders in pregnant women and children, adhering to international toxicity benchmarks. Implemented a research methodology spanning in vitro experiments - animal models - human population studies.</li><li><strong>Achievements & Values:</strong> Developed a novel Pollutant-Disease Impact Assessment Framework that established standardized protocols for evaluating environmental contaminant risks, which provided critical theoretical foundations for methylmercury exposure prevention strategies. Achieved top 30% ranking in final research presentation evaluations.</li>',
    'projects.research.1.title': 'Research on Health Impacts of Methylmercury Exposure',
    'projects.research.2.desc': '<li><strong>Technical Application:</strong> Utilized Geographic Information System (GIS) to record waste generation points and integrated blockchain technology to enable full-process traceability of waste, thereby addressing the issue of data tampering in traditional tracking methods.</li><li><strong>Project Outcomes:</strong> Achieved a 40% waste recycling rate, and the team was awarded the "Innovative Waste Elimination" certificate.</li>',
    'projects.research.2.title': 'EMAHK Waste Challenge: Hysan Waste Tracking Initiative',
    'projects.research.3.desc': '<li><strong>Risk Assessment:</strong> Examined the entire bread manufacturing process, identifying 3 categories of hazard factors: physical (foreign object contamination), chemical (additive overuse), and biological (microbial contamination), and established a risk-level evaluation matrix.</li><li><strong>Solution Delivery:</strong> Proposed risk control measures (including critical controls such as metal detection, strict oversight of ingredient sourcing, and standardized baking conditions) and developed an actionable HACCP implementation guide for the enterprise. The related assessment results achieved an A grade in the final presentation.</li>',
    'projects.research.3.title': 'HACCP System Research in a Bread Manufacturing Enterprise',
    'projects.research.4.desc': '<li><strong>Risk Analysis:</strong> Developed an occupational risk assessment model based on the ISO Occupational Health and Safety Management System, incorporating factors such as the characteristics of food-related goods, workers\' physical conditions, the inclination and roughness of transportation slopes, and the height of storage racks.</li><li><strong>Protection Strategies:</strong> Proposed preventive measures including forklift speed restrictions, anti-fall systems for racks, and PPE-based access control systems, projected to reduce work-related injury rates associated with goods handling by 35%.</li>',
    'projects.research.4.title': 'Research on Occupational Safety Management in High-Rise Racking Warehouses',
    'projects.research.5.desc': '<li><strong>Hardware Development:</strong> Utilized the Raspberry Pi as the main control core, integrating Dynamixel servos, HC-SR04 ultrasonic sensors, and an Intel RealSense D415 depth camera, while designing an expansion board and cooling system. Optimized serial communication protocols, improving hardware response speed by 60%, to address multi-module synchronization delays.</li><li><strong>Algorithm Implementation:</strong> Employed the LeNet convolutional neural network for fruit target recognition and developed an obstacle avoidance algorithm for 3D reconstruction and path planning. Iterated PID algorithm parameters, achieving positioning accuracy within ±3mm, to correct robotic arm positioning errors.</li><li><strong>Engineering Validation and Optimization:</strong> Conducted 5 functional tests, including obstacle avoidance and grasping in the laboratory to verify the robot\'s high recognition accuracy, positioning precision, and control stability. Optimized hardware communication efficiency and algorithm responsiveness, resulting in a deployable agricultural harvesting technology solution, with related findings being published in the domestic journal Modern Information Technology.</li>',
    'projects.research.5.title': 'Raspberry Pi-Based Deep Learning Harvesting Robot',
    'projects.research.6.desc': '<li><strong>Technical Innovation:</strong> Collaborated with the team to conduct studies on soil heavy metals, fly ash, and biochar, participating in experiments such as pH measurement and sludge water filtration. Innovatively designed a four-stage treatment device integrating "magnetic-modified biochar + spherical nylon mesh," achieving a closed-loop process of "adsorption-regeneration-recycling".</li><li><strong>Research Value:</strong> The device enabled wastewater treatment & soil remediation, supporting corporate green transformation & delivering environmental/social/economic benefits. The core technology was developed into a patent-level solution, which successfully secured the Internet Plus College Students Innovation and Entrepreneurship Project, further supporting corporate sustainability.</li>',
    'projects.research.6.title': 'R&D of a Magnetic-Modified Biochar Device for Soil Heavy Metal Remediation',
